<CATEGORY> sports </CATEGORY>
<HEADLINE> Bills' Smith Skips Out To See Dad </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	ORCHARD PARK, N.Y. (AP) -- Buffalo Bills defensive end Bruce  
Smith took a second day off from practice Wednesday to be with his 
ailing father. 
</P>
<P>
	Smith said he'll rejoin the team Thursday.  
</P>
<P>
	``He's still in the hospital right now,'' Smith said in a  
telephone interview. ``I'm coming back tonight. I can sit down and 
talk more about it tomorrow.'' 
</P>
<P>
	Smith's father, George, has been troubled by several ailments  
including emphysema. He is in a rehabilitation center near Smith's 
home in Norfolk, Va. 
</P>
<P>
	Smith wouldn't be specific about his father's condition or say  
if it were immediately life-threatening. ``It's really a number of 
things that he's dealing with,'' Smith said. 
</P>
<P>
	The oft-injured veteran defensive end credits his father for  
inspiring him to keep playing -- and to play through the pain. 
</P>
<P>
	``The doctors wrote him off about six or seven years ago,''  
Smith said last month. ``They said he had six months to live, and 
my father's still hanging around. He's not in very good shape but 
he's still passing on knowledge and experiences and wisdom, and 
that's where I get my will to keep pushing on.'' 
  	   	
</P>
</TEXT>
