<HEADLINE> Bengals Release DB, Waive Punter </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	CINCINNATI (AP) -- The Cincinnati Bengals released defensive back  
Thomas Randolph and waived punter Brad Costello on Wednesday. 
</P>
<P>
	Randolph, a sixth-year cornerback, was acquired in March 1998 as  
an unrestricted free agent from the New York Giants. He started one 
game and played in all 16 last season. 
</P>
<P>
	Costello, who tore a muscle in his right hip during the  
preseason, was waived with an undisclosed injury settlement. 
Costello signed with Cincinnati as a rookie free agent last year 
and appeared in three games. 
  	   	
</P>
