<CATEGORY> sports </CATEGORY>
<HEADLINE> Griffith Named WNBA's Most Valuable </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	NEW YORK (AP) -- Yolanda Griffith of the Sacramento Monarch  
completed a triple sweep today by being selected the WNBA's Most 
Valuable Player. 
</P>
<P>
	She earlier won the Newcomer of the Year and Defensive Player  
awards. 
</P>
<P>
	Griffith beat out Sheryl Swoopes of the Houston Comets in the  
voting for the MVP award. 
</P>
<P>
	She received 397 points and 23 first place votes. Swoopes got  
364 points and 15-first place votes. Swoopes' Houston teammate 
Cynthia Cooper, a two-time WNBA MVP, got 324 points and 13 
first-place votes. 
</P>
<P>
	Griffith averaged league-best averages of 11.3 in rebounds and  
2.52 in steal and also finished second in scoring (18.8 ppg) and 
field goal percentage (.541). 
</P>
<P>
	The award is presented by Buick.  
  	   	
</P>
