<HEADLINE> Dow Gains 40 in Early Trading / Wall Street Report  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	NEW YORK (AP) -- The Dow Jones industrial average is up 40 points  
in today's early going. 
</P>
<P>
	The Dow had fallen almost 500 points in the last four sessions.  
Since an all-time high closing of 11,326.04 last Wednesday, the Dow 
fell 496.76, or 4.3 percent, to 10,829.28, yesterday's closing 
figure. 
</P>
<P>
	Advancers on the New York Stock Exchange hold a 9-5 lead over  
decliners today. 
</P>
<P>
	The Nasdaq Composite Index is up 12 points and the S&AMP;P 500 Index  
is up four points. 
</P>
<P>
	Wall Street is looking to start September in a different fashion  
than it ended August. 
</P>
<P>
	While overseas markets generally have moved higher today, there  
are still some concerns for investors. 
</P>
<P>
	The fear of higher interest rates remains, especially with the  
all-important August unemployment report due Friday. 
</P>
<P>
	And bond prices are a little weaker again today as the dollar  
continues its struggles against the Japanese yen. 
  	   	
</P>
