<CATEGORY> sports </CATEGORY>
<HEADLINE> Star 2-Year-Old Out of Hopeful </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	SARATOGA SPRINGS, N.Y. (AP) -- More Than Ready, unbeaten in five  
starts and generally considered the leading 2-year-old colt in 
training, will not start in the $200,000 Hopeful on Saturday at 
Saratoga because of a slight fever. 
</P>
<P>
	``It's disappointing because the Hopeful was the race we were  
pointing for and we had thirty days to gear up for it,'' trainer 
Todd Pletcher said of the colt, who in his fifth start and fourth 
stakes won the Sanford by 9 3/4 lengths July 29 at Saratoga. 
</P>
<P>
	``We're playing it very conservatively,'' Pletcher added  
Wednesday. ``With a horse of this magnitude, I think that's the way 
to play it.'' 
</P>
<P>
	With the Breeders' Cup Juvenile on Nov. 6 at Gulfstream Park  
still his ultimate goal, More Than Ready is now expected to start 
in the Futurity on Sept. 19 and the Champagne on Oct. 9, both at 
Belmont Park. 
</P>
<P>
	Noting that ``the colt was a little quiet'' after Sunday's  
five-furlong workout over Saratoga's training track, Pletcher had 
him scoped. The procedure revealed the presence of a small amount 
of mucous. The colt's temperature was also 101.3, nearly a degree 
higher than usual. 
</P>
<P>
	``The fact that it was a little higher concerned us,'' Pletcher  
said, ``so we pulled some blood on him and his white count came 
back slightly elevated, indicative that he was possibly coming down 
with a virus or bug.'' 
</P>
<P>
	After having been walked an extra day, another blood test was  
taken. The second test results showed the white count improved but 
still not ideal, and the decision not to run him the Hopeful 
followed. 
  	   	
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
