<HEADLINE> Lewinsky on Mission to Slim Down </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	SAN DIEGO (AP) -- Monica Lewinsky is on a mission to slim down.  
</P>
<P>
	The former White House intern announced she has been enrolled at  
a Jenny Craig Inc.'s weight loss program since earlier this summer. 
</P>
<P>
	``Anyone who has struggled with excess weight knows that this is  
a very personal issue, and it's not easy to talk about,'' said Ms. 
Lewinsky, in a statement released today on the company's Internet 
site. 
</P>
<P>
	Jenny Craig, the company's co-founder, said that Ms. Lewinsky  
has been motivated since starting the program and is ``progressing 
toward her goals.'' 
</P>
<P>
	The company did not say how much weight Ms. Lewinsky intends to  
lose. Ms. Lewinsky, whose affair with President Clinton led to his 
impeachment, meets regularly with a program consultant to plan 
weekly menus and get suggestions on exercise. 
</P>
<P>
	Ms. Lewinsky has not been paid to endorse the diet program and  
is being treated just like any other client, said company spokesman 
Brian Luscomb. Some clients of the diet program are featured in 
company commercials, but Ms. Lewinsky is not scheduled to appear in 
any of the ads, he said. 
</P>
<P>
	Jenny Craig Inc., based in La Jolla, Calif., has approximately  
750 weight loss centers worldwide. 




  	   	
</P>
</TEXT>
