<HEADLINE> McGwire Hits 52nd Home Run </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	ST. LOUIS (AP) -- Mark McGwire ended a 25-at-bat drought with his  
52nd home run and became the career leader in homers by a first 
baseman Wednesday night. 
</P>
<P>
	McGwire hit a 1-0 pitch from Ryan Dempster off the scoreboard in  
left field, a drive estimated at 459 feet, for his first homer in 
eight games. That left him three behind major-league leader Sammy 
Sosa of the Chicago Cubs. 
</P>
<P>
	The drought was McGwire's longest since a stretch of 32 at-bats  
from June 9-19. His longest this season is 40 at-bats. 
</P>
<P>
	McGwire has hit 494 home runs as a first baseman, one more than  
Lou Gehrig. 
  	   	
