<HEADLINE> More Than 78,000 T-shirts Recalled </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	WASHINGTON (AP) -- Clothing designer GUESS? is recalling more  
than 78,000 girls' T-shirts with a liquid-filled bubble patch on 
the front. 
</P>
<P>
	The Consumer Product Safety Commission said Tuesday the liquid  
contains a petroleum distillate that can be harmful if ingested. 
</P>
<P>
	The bubble patches come in three shapes -- a heart, a circle and  
a rectangle -- with liquids in three different color combinations. 
</P>
<P>
	The T-shirts were sold in clothing stores nationwide from June  
1997 through March 1999 in sizes small through extra large. They 
cost $10 to $26 depending on the style. 
</P>
<P>
	Customers should stop wearing the T-shirts immediately and  
return them to the store where they were purchased for a refund, 
the commission said. 
  	   	
</P>
