<CATEGORY> sports </CATEGORY>
<HEADLINE> Indians' CF Lofton Comes Off DL </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	CLEVELAND (AP) -- Cleveland Indians center fielder Kenny Lofton  
was activated from the disabled list Wednesday after missing most 
of the last month with an injured hamstring. 
</P>
<P>
	Lofton, who was back in the lineup for Wednesday's game against  
Anaheim, has appeared in just one game since July 27. He aggravated 
the injury in his only game back on Aug. 14 against Baltimore and 
returned to the disabled list. 
</P>
<P>
	``Kenny said he was ready, that he wanted to play and so that's  
it,'' Cleveland manager Mike Hargrove said. 
</P>
<P>
	Lofton is hitting .306 with six home runs and 24 stolen bases  
this season. 
</P>
<P>
	Cleveland also purchased the contract of starter Jim Brower from  
Triple-A Buffalo. Brower, 26, posted an 11-11 record with Buffalo 
this season and has never played in the major leagues before. 
  	   	
</P>
</TEXT>
