<CATEGORY> sports </CATEGORY>
<HEADLINE> Blackhawks Sign Goaltender Thibault </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	CHICAGO (AP) -- The Chicago Blackhawks have signed goaltender  
Jocelyn Thibault and two defensemen to multi-year contracts, the 
team announced today. 
</P>
<P>
	The Blackhawks acquired Thibault from the Montreal Canadiens  
last November, along with Dave Manson and Brad Brown in exchange 
for Jeff Hackett, Eric Weinrich, Alain Nasreddine and future 
considerations. 
</P>
<P>
	Thibault was originally the first round pick of the Quebec  
Nordiques in the 1993 entry draft. He was traded to Montreal after 
two seasons. 
</P>
<P>
	Last season, Thibault had a 21-26-5 record with four shutouts  
for the Blackhawks. He also became just the fifth goalie in NHL 
history to win his 100th career game before the age of 25. He 
joined Patrick Roy, Martin Brodeur, Tom Barrasso and Grant Fuhr in 
that elite club. 
</P>
<P>
	The Blackhawks also signed deals with Brown and Jamie Allison,  
both restricted free agents. 
</P>
<P>
	Brown played in six games with the Blackhawks last season,  
scoring one goal, with seven assists and 205 penalty minutes. 
Allison, acquired last season in a trade with the Calgary Flames, 
appeared in 39 games with the Blackhawks with two goals and two 
assists. 
  	   	
</P>
</TEXT>
