<DOCNO> APW19990901.0106 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1999-09-01 13:20:20 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<CATEGORY> sports </CATEGORY>
<HEADLINE> NBA Schedules 119 Preseason Games </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	NEW YORK (AP) -- The Miami Heat will be the first NBA team to  
play an exhibition game in Israel when it meets perennial national 
champion Maccabi Oct. 11 at Tel Eviv. 
</P>
<P>
	Preseason games also will be played in Italy and Mexico, it was  
announced Wednesday. 
</P>
<P>
	The exhibition schedule lists 119 games in five countries, 34  
states and three Canadian provinces. It begins Oct. 10. 
</P>
<P>
	Another feature of the schedule is the McDonald's Championship,  
regarded as the world club championships. NBA champion San Antonio 
will play five other champion teams from around the world Oct. 
14-16 at Milan, Italy. 
</P>
<P>
	Also participating will be the EuroLeague's Zalgiris Kaunas of  
Lithuania, the Varese Roosters of Italy, Brazil's Vasco de Gama of 
the South American Basketball Club League, CS Sagesse of Lebanon 
and the Adelaide 36ers of Australia's National Basketball League. 
</P>
<P>
	The NBA returns to Mexico City on October 24 when the Golden  
State Warriors play the New Jersey Nets. 
</P>
<P>
	The Naismith Cup, between Canada's Vancouver Grizzlies and the  
Toronto Raptors, will be played in Edmonton, Alberta. 
</P>
<P>
	The exhibition schedule ends Oct. 29 and the NBA's regular  
season begins Nov. 2 with 26 of the league's 29 teams playing. 
  	   	
</P>
</TEXT>
