</P>
<P>
	LOS ANGELES (AP) -- Hilton Hotels Corp. said today it is in  
discussions about a possible merger with Promus Hotel Corp. In a 
brief news release, Hilton said it had begun talks with Promus 
about ``a possible business combination.'' The company said there 
was no assurance a deal would be reached. A call placed to Memphis, 
Tenn.-based Promus before business hours was not immediately 
returned. In the past Hilton has expressed interest in buying 
Promus, but executives have said that the company was too pricey. 
Promus had $1.1 billion in revenues in 1998, while Hilton showed 
$1.8 billion for the same period. 

</P>
<P>
