today to approve the company's acquisition of Atlantic Richfield 
Co., which will create one of the world's largest energy companies. 
The yes vote was 99.3 percent vote, the same percentage by which 
Atlantic Richfield shareholders had voted earlier this week in Los 
Angeles. BP Amoco shareholders also approved today a split of BP 
Amoco shares which will have the effect of doubling the shares on 
issue. 

