<CATEGORY> financial </CATEGORY>
<HEADLINE> Priceline.com To Offer Mortgages </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	STAMFORD, Conn. (AP) -- Priceline.com and Alliance Capital  
Partners today announced a joint venture that will allow consumers 
to set the prices and terms they want to pay for home mortgages. 
</P>
<P>
	The service called Pricelinemortgage will allow consumers to  
find out within minutes if they have been approved for financing, 
the companies said today in a statement. 
</P>
<P>
	The service, which debuts after Labor Day, uses Fannie Mae's  
automated underwriting system to speed the application process. 
</P>
<P>
	When a borrower's ``name-your-own-rate'' offer is accepted,  
Pricelinemortgage provides a locked-in rate. It also guarantees 
closing costs and says it can save consumers up to $1,000 in 
closing costs compared to other online and conventional lenders. 
</P>
<P>
	Priceline.com has been offering name-your-price mortgages,  
refinancing and home equity loans through LendingTree Inc. since 
February and says it will continue that relationship. 
</P>
<P>
	Based in Stamford, Priceline.com allows Internet users to name  
their own prices for automobiles, lodging, airline tickets and 
other products and services. 
</P>
<P>
	Alliance Capital is a unitary thrift holding company in  
Jacksonville, Fla. 



</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
