<CATEGORY> sports </CATEGORY>
<HEADLINE> Sosa Hits 56th Homer </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	SAN DIEGO (AP) -- Sammy Sosa hit his major league-leading 56th  
homer Wednesday night, a solo shot in the fourth inning to 
straightaway center field off San Diego Padres left-hander Sterling 
Hitchcock. 
</P>
<P>
	The ball went an estimated 431 feet, hitting a television camera  
on a platform that juts out from the permanent wall. Sosa had been 
2-for-14 (.143) lifetime against Hitchcock, with no homers. 
</P>
<P>
	It was Sosa's second homer in as many nights and his 13th in 18  
games. Sosa has 26 career homers against San Diego, the second most 
against any team. He has 30 against Colorado. 
</P>
<P>
	The homer gave the Cubs a 1-0 lead and allowed Sosa to stay four  
ahead of Mark McGwire, who hit his 52nd earlier Wednesday night. 
  	   	
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
