<HEADLINE> Phi Beta Doc Sets Saranac Record </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	SARATOGA SPRINGS, N.Y. (AP) -- Phi Beta Doc won the Saranac  
Handicap in track-record time on Wednesday, beating favored 
Monarch's Maze by 2 1/4 lengths in the 92nd running of the $111,700 
stake for 3-year-olds on turf. 
</P>
<P>
	Phi Beta Doc, ridden by Ramon Dominguez, went 1 3-16 miles in  
1:51 3-5, 3-5 of a second faster than the mark set by 
Heavenannaturesing in 1997. 
</P>
<P>
	Monarch's Maze was a length ahead of Big Rascal in the  
eight-horse field. 
</P>
<P>
	Phi Beta Doc, winning his third race in six starts this year,  
earned $67,020 for owner Dennis Foster and co-owner and trainer 
Robert Leonard. 
</P>
<P>
	The winner returned $10, $3.70 and $2.40. Monarch's Maze paid $3  
and $2.60 and Big Rascal was worth $3.90. 
  	   	
