<CATEGORY> entertainment </CATEGORY>
<HEADLINE> Upcoming Celebrity Birthdays  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 *Celebrity Spotlight &AMP; Birthdays    	

</P>
<P>
	Harry Connick Jr. is the voice of beatnik artist Dean in the  
summer movie ``Iron Giant.'' His new collection of vocal jazz, 
``Come by Me,'' was released this summer by Columbia. One reviewer 
wrote: ``After his failed electric jazz-funk-fusion experiment, 
`She,' Connick has refocused himself on what he does best, taking 
almost full control of this project and his 16-piece big band and a 
full orchestra.'' Connick was born on Sept. 11, 1967. 

</P>
<P>
	David Arquette, born on Sept. 8, 1971, and Courteney Cox met on  
the set of ``Scream'' and dated for nearly two years before 
Arquette proposed. They were married in a star-studded ceremony in 
San Francisco in June. Arquette and his wife star in the upcoming 
``Scream 3.'' 

</P>
<P>
	``Cruel Intentions'' co-stars Ryan Phillippe and Reese  
Witherspoon were married in June in a ceremony in South Carolina. 
Phillippe was born on Sept. 10, 1974. His film credits also include 
``I Know What You Did Last Summer'' and ``54.'' 

</P>
<P>
	Michelle Williams has appeared on stage naked and has been on  
her own since 15. On top of that, she plays a bad girl on 
television's ``Dawson's Creek.'' Williams, who was born on Sept. 9, 
1980, moved to Los Angeles from San Diego -- alone -- to pursue her 
acting career. ``I had the `from-birth-to-16-year-old' blues. It 
was a perpetual mood in my life,'' she said. ``So I moved out. I 
don't know if I was ready, but I was determined.'' 

</P>
<P>
	Celebrity birthdays Sept. 5-11:  
</P>
<P>
	Sept. 5: Comedian-actor Bob Newhart is 70. Actor William Devane  
is 60. Actress Raquel Welch is 59. Singer Loudon Wainwright III is 
53. TV personality-musician Dweezil Zappa is 30. Actress Rose 
McGowan (``Scream'') is 25. 
</P>
<P>
	Sept. 6: Comedian JoAnne Worley is 62. Actress Swoosie Kurtz is  
