<HEADLINE> Eagles Get GB's Michels for Harris </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	PHILADELPHIA (AP) -- The Philadelphia Eagles and Green Bay  
Packers traded first-round disappointments on Wednesday, the Eagles 
sending defensive end Jon Harris to Green Bay in return for 
offensive tackle John Michels. 
</P>
<P>
	Each rejoins a former coach -- Harris will play for former Eagles  
coach Ray Rhodes and Michels for former Packers assistant Andy 
Reid. 
</P>
<P>
	Harris, the 25th overall choice in the 1997 NFL draft, played 24  
games in two seasons, with eight starts. He had 73 total tackles 
and two quarterback sacks. Michels was the 27th player selected in 
the 1996 draft 
</P>
<P>
	He started nine games as a rookie and then five more in 1997.  
Last year, Michels tore the anterior cruciate ligament in his right 
knee and missed the entire season. 
</P>
<P>
	Reid said Michels would compete for a starting job in  
Philadelphia. 
  	   	
</P>
