<CATEGORY> financial </CATEGORY>
<HEADLINE> European Stocks Close Lower </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	LONDON (AP) -- Spurred by weakness in the bond market hurting  
insurers and a decline in pharmaceutical shares headed by 
SmithKline Beecham, European stocks fell to their lowest point 
Tuesday in a week and a half. 
</P>
<P>
	Allianz AG, the biggest stock in the Dow Jones Stoxx Insurance  
index, closed with a loss of 7.30 euros, at 247.00 euros, while in 
London, Allied Zurich was the worst blue-chip performer, with a 
loss of 45.5 pence to 760.5 pence. Banks and insurance companies 
hold large bond portfolios and are more sensitive to rising 
interest rates. 
</P>
<P>
	SmithKline led the drop in European pharmaceutical stocks after  
the U.S. Food and Drug Administration requested modifications to 
its license application for Bexxar leukemia treatment. Its shares 
closed down 26 pence at 810.5 pence. 
</P>
<P>
	The Dow Jones Stoxx Index of 592 European companies fell 5.89  
points, or 1.9 percent, to close at 308.69. 
</P>
<P>
	The Dow Jones Euro Stoxx Index, which tracks 297 companies in  
countries that joined the single currency, closed down 5.89 points 
at 323.44. 
</P>
<P>
	The Dow Jones Euro Stoxx 50 Index fell 68.56 points to 3,769.14,  
while the DJ Stoxx 50 Index closed down 75.64 points at 3,699.76. 
</P>
<P>
	French retailers outperformed in domestic markets, prompting  
gains among other European food retailers as talk about 
consolidation proliferated. 
</P>
<P>
	On Monday, Carrefour announced it was proposing a friendly euros  
15.6 billion all-share takeover of Promodes, creating the world's 
second-largest supermarket retailer. 
</P>
<P>
	In Paris, Carrefour's stock rose 13.60 euros to 154.00 euros,  
and Promodes jumped 64.00 euros to 893.00 euros. In London, Tesco 
and Sainsbury were the best blue-chip performers, gaining 7.25 
pence to 184.25 pence and 7 pence to 429 pence, respectively. 
</P>
<P>
	Nevertheless, the Paris CAC-40 index closed down 1.5 percent to  
4,589.22. 
</P>
<P>
	Frankfurt's Xetra DAX index fell 2.25 percent to 5,270.77,  
Milan's MIBtel index fell 1.9 percent to 33,627, Amsterdam's AEX 
Index fell 2.0 percent to 572.42 and London's FTSE 100 index of 
blue-chip shares closed down 2.0 percent at 6,246.4. 



  	   	
</P>
</TEXT>
