<DOCNO> APW19990901.0259 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1999-09-01 14:50:13 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<CATEGORY> financial </CATEGORY>
<HEADLINE> Big Movers in the Stock Market  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	NEW YORK (AP) -- Stocks that moved substantially or traded  
heavily Wednesday on the New York Stock Exchange and Nasdaq Stock 
Market. 

</P>
<P>
                               *NYSE    	

</P>
<P>
 *Promus Hotel Corp., up 2 15/16 at 32    	
</P>
<P>
	The Wall Street Journal reported in Wednesday's edition that  
Hilton Hotels Corp. is in discussions to purchase Promus in a deal 
that would be worth more than $2.4 billion. 

</P>
<P>
 *International Business Machines Corp., up 2 11/16 at 127 1/4    	
</P>
<P>
	IBM agreed Tuesday to sell its networking technology to market  
leader Cisco Systems Inc. The deal takes IBM out of the business of 
computer networking hardware after years of struggling in the 
lucrative market. 

</P>
<P>
 *H&AMP;R Block Inc., down 4 5/8 at 51    	
</P>
<P>
	The tax preparation and financial services firm will acquire  
Olde Financial Corp., the parent company of Olde Discount Corp., 
for $850 million in cash. H&AMP;R Block said the acquisition should 
begin adding to earnings in fiscal 2000. 

</P>
<P>
 *Wackenhut Corp., down 3 at 15 15/16    	
</P>
<P>
	The provider of security services and temporary staffing will  
discontinue its contract with Travis County, Texas, to operate the 
county's 1,000-bed Community Justice Center. Wackenhut signed a new 
deal to provide security services to Commonwealth Edison plants. 

</P>
<P>
 *GP Strategies, up 3 9/16 at 11 3/8    	
</P>
<P>
	The company, a provider of technical and management training,  
received a buyout offer of about $149.6 million from its management 
and an equity investment fund run by Veronis Suhler &AMP; Associates 
Communications Partners. 

</P>
<P>
                              *NASDAQ   	

</P>
<P>
 *Premier Laser Systems Inc., up 2 1/4 at 4    	
</P>
<P>
	The Irvine, Calif., maker of diagnostic and therapeutic products  
received approval from the U.S. Food and Drug Administration to 
market its BluLaze product for composite curing and teeth 
whitening. The product will sell for about $5,000. 

</P>
<P>
 *Staff Leasing Inc., up 2 at 11 1/4    	
</P>
<P>
	Staff Leasing's board is exploring strategic alternatives,  
including a sale or recapitalization. The human resources services 
company, which previously rejected an offer from Paribas Principal 
Partners, is now reconsidering its options. 

</P>
<P>
 *MMC Networks Inc., down 4 1/8 at 26 3/4    	
</P>
<P>
	Shares fell for a second straight session after IBM's decision  
to exit the business of making computer networking hardware. Since 
January, MMC Networks has sold network processor chips to IBM, 
accounting for a major share of its revenue. 

</P>
<P>
 *AutoImmune Inc., down 2 1/2 at 7/8    	
</P>
<P>
	The biopharmaceutical company will abandon development of  
rheumatoid arthritis drug Colloral after the drug didn't meet its 
meet its primary objective. An analyst said AutoImmune has no other 
significant drugs in late-stage development. 




  	   	
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
