<CATEGORY> financial </CATEGORY>
<HEADLINE> Milk Cooperatives Market Together </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	SYRACUSE, N.Y. (AP) -- Dairylea Cooperative on Wednesday  
announced the formation of a joint milk marketing venture with 
Missouri-based Dairy Farmers of America, one of the largest dairy 
cooperatives in the world. 
</P>
<P>
	Dairy Marketing Services expects to market nearly 10 billion  
pounds of milk annually in the Northeast. Together, the two 
cooperatives manage about 35 percent of the Northeast's milk 
supply. 
</P>
<P>
	The two companies' membership activities and services and all  
businesses will remain separate. But the milk marketing 
cooperatives expect to save their members as much as $5 million per 
year in transportation costs. 
</P>
<P>
	``This is a giant step of cooperation in the Northeast,'' said  
Lewis Gardner, a dairy farmer from Galeton, Pa., and a DFA regional 
chairman. ``Both DFA and Dairylea have milk trucks traveling the 
same roads. We also serve many of the same customers. By working 
together, we can reduce our marketing costs significantly.'' 
</P>
<P>
	Milk will be provided by more than 6,000 farmers located  
throughout New England, New York, Pennsylvania, Delaware, Maryland, 
West Virginia and New Jersey, said Clyde Rutherford, president of 
Syracuse-based Dairylea. 
</P>
<P>
	The new company will serve more than 90 fluid milk and  
manufacturing customers in the area, Rutherford said. Major 
customers of the Dairy Marketing Services include Suiza Foods, 
Kraft Foods, Great Lakes Cheese, Leprino Foods, H.P. Hood and 
Sorrento Cheese. 
</P>
<P>
	Dairylea is owned by 2,600 farmers throughout the Northeast. It  
markets about 5 billion pounds of milk annually and participates in 
a milk marketing network stretching from Maine to Maryland to Ohio. 
</P>
<P>
	Dairy Farmers of America is based in Kansas City and has 25,000  
members in 45 states. It operates 33 manufacturing plants in 15 
states producing dairy products, including cheese, butter, 
condensed milk, cream cheese, nonfat dry milk, dehydrated dairy 
products and a variety of whey products. 
</P>
<P>
	The new company will be based in Syracuse.  


  	   	
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
